ce:section.ce:para:
In order to validate the feasibility of the fabricated sensor for practical applications, the CD-QT system was applied to detect Al3+ in real samples such as laboratory tap water. The fluorescence emission spectra of the CD-QT system were recorded in the absence of any added aluminium ions and after the addition of various Al3+ concentrations (5–300 µM) by standard addition method and the results are shown in Fig. 5
                           a. The recovery study of Al3+ in tap water samples was performed and the results were summarized in (Table.2
                           ).The average relative standard deviation (RSD) was found to be 0.28 % which clearly demonstrates the suitability of the CD-QT system as a promising and reliable sensor for Al3+ detection with good accuracy and precision.
